**Overall Meaning:**

This verse warns against negligence in the pursuit of Brahman-realization. It emphasizes that carelessness or laxity in this pursuit is equivalent to death, as it hinders progress towards liberation. Those who speak of Brahman consider negligence a fatal flaw in the path of knowledge.

**Translation:**

**Negligence in steadfastness in Brahman should never be done. Those who speak of Brahman say that negligence is death in the pursuit of knowledge.** 
